<li id="cite_note-79"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFPatersonRossow1999" class="citation journal cs1">Paterson, Frances R. A.; Rossow, Lawrence F. (May 1999). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://online.ucpress.edu/abt/article-abstract/61/5/358/16001/Chained-to-the-Devil-s-Throne-Evolution-amp">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>"Chained to the Devil's Throne": Evolution &amp; Creation Science as a Religio-Political Issue"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_American_Biology_Teacher" class="mw-redirect" title="The American Biology Teacher">The American Biology Teacher</a></i>. <b>61</b> (5): 358. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.2307%2F4450698">10.2307/4450698</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/4450698">4450698</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+American+Biology+Teacher&amp;rft.atitle=%22Chained+to+the+Devil%27s+Throne%22%3A+Evolution+%26+Creation+Science+as+a+Religio-Political+Issue&amp;rft.volume=61&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=358&amp;rft.date=1999-05&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F4450698&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F4450698%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft.aulast=Paterson&amp;rft.aufirst=Frances+R.+A.&amp;rft.au=Rossow%2C+Lawrence+F.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fonline.ucpress.edu%2Fabt%2Farticle-abstract%2F61%2F5%2F358%2F16001%2FChained-to-the-Devil-s-Throne-Evolution-amp&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1975" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Smith, Joseph Fielding</a> (1975). <span class="id-lock-limited" title="Free access subject to limited trial, subscription normally required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/books/edition/Answers_to_Gospel_Questions/UmuosMjT_KMC?hl=en&amp;gbpv=0"><i>Answers to Gospel Questions</i></a></span>. Vol.&#160;5. <a href="/wiki/Deseret_Book" class="mw-redirect" title="Deseret Book">Deseret Book</a>. p.&#160;116 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Answers+to+Gospel+Questions&amp;rft.pages=116&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft.date=1975&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Fielding&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2FAnswers_to_Gospel_Questions%2FUmuosMjT_KMC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-81"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-81">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMarrott" class="citation web cs1">Marrott, Robert L. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20170915230627/http://emp.byui.edu/marrottr/SevenDeadlyAnderson.pdf">"The Seven Deadly Heresies (Tape Transcript)"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University-Idaho" class="mw-redirect" title="Brigham Young University-Idaho">Brigham Young University-Idaho</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://emp.byui.edu/marrottr/SevenDeadlyAnderson.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on September 15, 2017<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">September 15,</span> 2017</span>. <q>There are those who say that revealed religion and organic evolution can be harmonized. This is both false and devilish ... there is no way to harmonize the revealed religion which has come to us, with the theoretical postulates of Darwinism and the diverse speculations descending therefrom. Do not be deceived and be lead&#32;&#91;<i><a href="/wiki/Sic" title="Sic">sic</a></i>&#93; to believe that the famous document of the First Presidency, issued in the day of President Joseph F. Smith and entitled The Origin of Man, means anything except exactly what it says. ... that there was no death in the world for him or for any form of life until after the fall .... Try as you may, you cannot harmonize these things with the evolutionary postulate that death has always existed and that the various forms of life have evolved from preceding forms over astronomically long periods of time. Try as you may, you cannot harmonize the theories of men with the inspired word .... If death has always prevailed in the world, there was no fall of Adam that brought death to all forms of life. If Adam did not fall, there is no need for an atonement. If there was no atonement there is no salvation ... If there is no salvation there is no God.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Seven+Deadly+Heresies+%28Tape+Transcript%29&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University-Idaho&amp;rft.aulast=Marrott&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+L.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Femp.byui.edu%2Fmarrottr%2FSevenDeadlyAnderson.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-82">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMcConkie2003" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce</a> (2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/teaching-seminary-preservice-readings-religion-370-471-and-475/the-bible-a-sealed-book?lang=eng&amp;query=evolution">"The Bible, a Sealed Book"</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/teaching-seminary-preservice-readings-religion-370-471-and-475?lang=eng"><i>Teaching Seminary: Preservice Readings</i></a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=The+Bible%2C+a+Sealed+Book&amp;rft.btitle=Teaching+Seminary%3A+Preservice+Readings&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.aulast=McConkie&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruce&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fmanual%2Fteaching-seminary-preservice-readings-religion-370-471-and-475%2Fthe-bible-a-sealed-book%3Flang%3Deng%26query%3Devolution&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-83"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-83">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMcConkie1984" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce R.</a> (October 1984). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/general-conference/1984/10/the-caravan-moves-on?lang=eng">"The Caravan Moves On"</a>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. <q>There is no salvation in a system of religion that rejects the doctrine of the Fall or that assumes man is the end product of evolution and so was not subject to a fall. True believers know that this earth and man and all forms of life were created in an Edenic, or paradisiacal, state in which there was no mortality, no procreation, no death.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Caravan+Moves+On&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=1984-10&amp;rft.aulast=McConkie&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruce+R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fgeneral-conference%2F1984%2F10%2Fthe-caravan-moves-on%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-MD-84"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-MD_84-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MD_84-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-MD_84-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMcConkie1958" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce</a> (1958). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/mormon-doctrine-1958-bruce-r-mc-conkie-lds/page/696/mode/1up"><i>Mormon Doctrine</i></a> (1st&#160;ed.). Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Bookcraft" title="Bookcraft">Bookcraft</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780884940623" title="Special:BookSources/9780884940623"><bdi>9780884940623</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Internet_Archives" class="mw-redirect" title="Internet Archives">Internet Archives</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Doctrine&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.edition=1st&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft.date=1958&amp;rft.isbn=9780884940623&amp;rft.aulast=McConkie&amp;rft.aufirst=Bruce&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fmormon-doctrine-1958-bruce-r-mc-conkie-lds%2Fpage%2F696%2Fmode%2F1up&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
