<li id="cite_note-88"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-88">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.pewforum.org/2007/05/16/in-focus-mormonism-in-modern-america/">"In Focus: Mormonism in Modern America"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Pew_Research_Center" title="Pew Research Center">Pew Research Center</a>. May 16, 2007.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=In+Focus%3A+Mormonism+in+Modern+America&amp;rft.pub=Pew+Research+Center&amp;rft.date=2007-05-16&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewforum.org%2F2007%2F05%2F16%2Fin-focus-mormonism-in-modern-america%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-89">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFNelson1987" class="citation magazine cs1"><a href="/wiki/Russell_M._Nelson" title="Russell M. Nelson">Nelson, Russell M.</a> (October 1987). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/new-era/1987/10/the-magnificence-of-man?lang=eng">"The Magnificence of Man"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/New_Era_(magazine)" title="New Era (magazine)">New Era</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. <q>Through the ages, some without scriptural understanding have tried to explain our existence by pretentious words such as ex nihilo (out of nothing). Others have deduced that, because of certain similarities between different forms of life, there has been an organic evolution from one form to another. ... To me, such theories are unbelievable!</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=New+Era&amp;rft.atitle=The+Magnificence+of+Man&amp;rft.date=1987-10&amp;rft.aulast=Nelson&amp;rft.aufirst=Russell+M.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fnew-era%2F1987%2F10%2Fthe-magnificence-of-man%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-allen-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-allen_90-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAllen1978" class="citation book cs1">Allen, A. Lester (1978). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20190129181423/http://emp.byui.edu/firestonel/bio%20475/readings/science%20and%20religion%20readings/mormonism%20and%20evolution%20readings/Lester%20Allen.pdf"><i>How An LDS Biologist Resolves The Evolution Question</i></a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University%E2%80%93Idaho" title="Brigham Young University–Idaho">Brigham Young University–Idaho</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://emp.byui.edu/firestonel/bio%20475/readings/science%20and%20religion%20readings/mormonism%20and%20evolution%20readings/Lester%20Allen.pdf">the original</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> on January 29, 2019.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=How+An+LDS+Biologist+Resolves+The+Evolution+Question&amp;rft.pub=Brigham+Young+University%E2%80%93Idaho&amp;rft.date=1978&amp;rft.aulast=Allen&amp;rft.aufirst=A.+Lester&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Femp.byui.edu%2Ffirestonel%2Fbio%2520475%2Freadings%2Fscience%2520and%2520religion%2520readings%2Fmormonism%2520and%2520evolution%2520readings%2FLester%2520Allen.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+views+on+evolution" class="Z3988"></span></span>
